Mike,

	Actually SMTP can say four things when a mail address is presented:

1)	Gulp. aka 250

2)	Not here, but I'll forward for you. aka 251

3)	Not here, you got to forward it yourself. aka 551

4)	No such destination, temporary errors, ... aka various codes

The intelligence of mail senders and receivers varies a bit in this
regard.  Some receivers gulp everything and decide later what to do.
Some senders grok the 251, RSET the connection, and forward it
themselves.  You can find dozens of other behaviours.  For your
application, the 251 should work just fine, if not you could lie and
250.

paul

